Nigerian singer Paul Okoye of the P-Square duo has revealed that he paid N70,000 to receive N40,000. He made this known via his Instastories on Thursday. The singer stated that he had to buy money so that he can pay for a visa fee at an embassy. READ MORE: “You Just Erased Your Father’s History” – Peter Okoye Slams Seun Kuti For Calling Peter Obi ‘Opportunist’ He wrote, ” Oooh!!! I buy money today!! Just because I have to pay for a certain visa fee in an embassy and it has to be paid in cash. ” Joke apart, I bought 40k with 70k. Aahhhh!!!!!!!! Naija breaking new records.”